item.dc:creator: @zi0 zi0
item.description:
@zi0 wrote:

[quote=“Riley111, post:53, topic:310362”][quote author=14-08 link=topic=406792.msg3006528#msg3006528 date=1256445227]
People shouldn’t have anything against a swastika being used on a model. But the fact that you called it a ‘German cape’ when really it should be called something entirely different. A NAZI was a member of Hitler’s party in World War II. So why would consider a German person to be a NAZI.
[/quote]
This is incorrect… ‘Nazi’ is a political party and was not only during WWII. Nazi’s still exist today and in fact, some goverments are still concidered to be ‘Nazi’. as for was was said about being apart of Hitler’s party. You can go against everything Hitler did and do not have to be in his part in order to be Nazi. And it is not only Germans that can be Nazi, anyone can.[/quote]

^^ that and the fact that the swastika was/is not only a symbol for Nazis. it has been used it many different religions and cultures way before hitler used it. Hinduism uses the swastika as a sign for the creator god Brahma, or facing to the right it represents the evolution of the universe. Buddhism uses the symbol to represents universal harmony. Jainism uses it as a symbol for the seventh saint. the Chinese empress wu of the tang dynasty used it as a symbol for the sun…the Greek, Celtic, Finnish, Sami, Native Americans, Slavic, German and Jewish all used the symbol BEFORE hitler.

to insinuate that all Germans are nazis isn’t right, but to be offended by the swastika is stupid.
